==English==
===Noun===
'''bargaining power''' ({{plural}} '''bargaining powers''')

#(''economics'') refers to the ability to influence the setting of prices or wages, usually arising from some sort of [[monopoly]] or [[monopsony]] position -- or a non-[[equilibrium]] situation in the [[market]].

#(''business'') refers to the general concept of how much [[leverage]] or influence a bargainer has in the course of a negotiation.